AUDIO: 'Welcome to Runway Academy. Today we\'re exploring a featured workflow called Character Creator. [music] Workflows is an amazing tool to use for'

[00:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'character creation as it allows you to generate anything that you need all at once. Let\'s explore this character creator workflow, which you can access yourself in the featured workflows section of workflows.'

[00:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Our first node is the prompt for the character description, which then gets fed into an LLM node to be enhanced with some custom system instructions. The LLM node is helping to describe the character in more detail, as well as'

[00:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'adding some rules, such as making sure the character is always pictured in a full body, neutral, forward- facing pose towards the camera with their whole face and front body visible. and the background always being described verbatim as a flat chroma green'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'background color with no shadows. From there, our first character image gets created. That character image is going to serve as our global foundational image reference so that the character stays consistent in every single'

[01:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generation. The first set of images that get created are neutral expression, full body, and close-ups. The prompts for each of these is quite simple. From there, the character gets created in three distinct poses. T-pose, right'

[01:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'profile, and left profile. These poses get generated with the help of a reference chart, which is plugged into image slot two, right underneath our global character reference image. Using charts or pose images in general, is a'

[01:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'great way to get your character looking exactly how you want. Let\'s quickly demonstrate getting our character into a new pose. Drag your main character reference image onto an empty part of the canvas to create a new image'

[01:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reference node. Then right click on the canvas and add a text node, another image upload node, and an image generation node. Hook up the text node to the prompt input, your main character reference into the image one input, and'

[01:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the empty image node into the image 2 input. Now upload any pose reference image. Then in the prompt box, say something like, "Show me the character from image one in the same pose as the'

[02:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reference from image two." Make sure the body proportions from image one stay the same. Now, your character will be in a new custom pose. Going back to the main workflow, now we have some additional images being created that showcase'

[02:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'various character expressions in both wide shots and close-ups. Surprised, angry, happy, bored, confused, and sad. All of the close-up images are using the'

[02:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'same text prompt node as our original close-up image that got created with a simple text prompt of zoom in and frame this exact character in a close-up. Under all of those image nodes, we have some video key frame nodes that are'

[02:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'using the wide full body shot as frame one and the close-up as the last frame, which creates a dynamic zoomin expressive video of your character. The prompt driving these nodes is quite simplistic and generic. The video'

[03:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'naturally and seamlessly transitions from the first frame to the last frame without cuts, transitions, or inconsistencies. [music] You can, of course, be more detailed about this prompt if you\'d like. Last but not least, we have some additional videos'

[03:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'being created. The first is a 360° character rotation plate. This node is very valuable if you need to extract any angle of your character. [music] Simply pause the video at the frame that you'

[03:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'need, right click on the node, and choose save video frame as to download it locally to your computer. And directly below that, we have the close-up image being fed into a video node with a prompt to get our character'

[03:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to speak. You can change the prompt to be whatever you\'d like, but the default here is just generic information that the model makes up. &gt;&gt; Hi, I\'m Alex. I really enjoy drawing cartoons in my free time, and my favorite dessert has to be chocolate'

